He got his revenge over arch rival Steve Ovett in the 1,500 metres final. Despite some political disapproval and the absence of the national anthem in the Olympic stadium, Coe showed himself to be the best of British, with 15 million watching on TV back home as he tried to win after Ovett's triumph in the 800 metres.  75 years ago (1947) A British South American Airways Avro Lancastrian airliner Star Dust crashed into Mount Tupungato in the Andes during a flight from Buenos Aires, Argentina to Santiago, Chile. The wreckage would not be found until 1998 when pieces of the aircraft emerged from the glacial ice. 42 years ago (1980) Eighty-five people died when a huge bomb exploded at Bologna railway station in Italy. The device went off in an air-conditioned waiting room packed with people escaping from the heat. Right-wing extremists were believed to be behind the attack which remains one of the deadliest in Italian history. 